        "timestamp": 1773482431,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. US deploys USS Tripoli amphibious assault ship to Middle East Middle East Issued on: 14/03/2026 - 11:00 The US is sending an amphibious assault ship, the USS Tripoli, and its Marine expeditionary unit to the Middle East according to a report by Axios quoting a senior US official. This includes personnel, F-35 fighter jets and warships. The decision comes as both President Trump and his defense secretary Pete Hegseth say the war is going very well for the United States. Story by Morgan Ayre. US military bombs military sites on Kharg island, Iranian media reports no damage 14/03/2026 Middle East War in the Middle East: A sailor stranded in the Gulf fears for his safety 13/03/2026 Middle East As 800,000 flee, half of Lebanon lives in war zones without markets, supplies or healthcare 13/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon’s Mission Impossible: Could US and Israeli pressure to disarm Hezbollah lead to civil war? 13/03/2026 Middle East Strait of Hormuz: Iran leverages control of a critical chokepoint in the global oil trade 13/03/2026 Middle East 'Mental, subjective impact': Iran taking on 'American might' with cyberterrorism 13/03/2026 Middle East Israel widens Lebanon bombing campaign to target north and central Beirut 13/03/2026 On the ground Middle East Netanyahu says new Iran leader 'can't show his face in public' 12/03/2026 Middle East Iran to allow India-flagged tankers to pass through Strait of Hormuz (reports) 12/03/2026 Middle East"
